title: Chemistry Cheating I
description:
PROBLEM DESCRIPTION.

As per normal in Giammanco’s Chemistry class, many students out of the M student class are going to cheat without repercussions on the upcoming test. However, only the first N students are competent and actually know what they are doing.

Due to seating arrangements, most students are only able to cheat off of a select few other students, where A cheating off B does not imply B can cheat off A. Cheating relations are transitive; i.e. if A can cheat off B and B can cheat off C, then A can cheat off C. A student’s grade is the number of competent people that they can cheat off of (either indirectly or directly, and may include themselves).

Everyone knows who everyone else is cheating off of (the students aren’t very stealthy, yet somehow the teacher doesn’t notice). Determine the highest grade of the class.

INPUT FORMAT.

  • The first line of input contains N and M, space separated.
  • The second line of input contains K, the total number of cheating “connections.”
  • The next K lines of input contain Ai and Bi, space separated, where person Ai cheats off of Bi.

OUTPUT FORMAT.

Print the highest grade of the class on a single line.

SAMPLE INPUT.

4 7
5
5 2
6 4
6 7
6 5
2 1

SAMPLE OUTPUT.

3
